Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.
Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{}
and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}.

Trim the @Baby Gem Lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a medium #bowl{}, combine the @Cider Vinegar{15%ml}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and
@Olive Oil for the Dressing{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the baby gem to the dressing, toss to coat, then set aside.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%g}. Fry until the mince has browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked
> when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic, @Tomato Puree{30%g}, and @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet} to the beef.
Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Honey{1%tbsp}, and @Water for the
Beef{100%ml}. Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the baby gem salad and spiced beef.

Sprinkle over the cheese and drizzle over the @Burger Sauce{45%g}.

Enjoy!